DataElement.preferredDefinition: The address of the manufacturer of the reprocessed medical device.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: information related to the manufacturer of equipment for reuse.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: Further or repeated use of equipment, instruments, devices, or materials. It includes additional use regardless of the original intent of the producer as to disposability or durability. It does not include the repeated use of fluids or solutions.

Concepts.definition: Further or repeated use of equipment, instruments, devices, or materials. It includes additional use regardless of the original intent of the producer as to disposability or durability. It does not include the repeated use of fluids or solutions.

Property.preferredDefinition: Manufacturer Name; the name of a business engaged in manufacturing some product

Concepts.definition: A person, enterprise, or entity that produces finished goods.

ConceptualDomain.preferredDefinition:
any unfavorable symptoms, signs, or disease temporally associated with the use of a medical
treatment or procedure that may or may not be considered related to the medical

ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: the address of the manufacturer of the reprocessed medical device.

ConceptualDomain.preferredDefinition: all components of an address, including building number, street name and type, city, state, postal code, and country.

RepresentationTerm.preferredDefinition: The location at which an organization or person can be reached. (from American Heritage Dictionary):Personal names, given or surname, as cultural characteristics, as ethnological or religious patterns, as indications of the geographic distribution of families and inbreeding, etc. Analysis of isonymy, the quality of having the same or similar names, is useful in the study of population genetics. NAMES is used also for the history of names or name changes of corporate bodies, such as medical societies, universities, hospitals, government agencies, etc.

Concepts.definition: A standardized representation of the location of a person, business, building, or organization.

A word or group of words indicating the identity of a person usually consisting of a first (personal) name and a last (family) name with an optional middle name. In some cultural traditions the family name comes first.
